          "architecture": {
            "features": [
              {
                "title": " ",
                "description": "Configured to use IBM secure by default standards, but can be edited to fit your use case."
              }
            ],
            "diagrams": [
              {
                "diagram": {
                  "caption": "Red Hat OpenShift cluster topology",
                  "url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/terraform-ibm-modules/terraform-ibm-base-ocp-vpc/refs/heads/da-improvement/reference-architecture/deployable-architecture-ocp-cluster.svg",
                  "type": "image/svg+xml"
                },
                "description": "This architecture supports creation of <b>Red Hat OpenShift cluster</b> on a Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) network. You can deploy the cluster on an existing VPC and this architecture supports creation of new VPC and subnets by selecting the VPC addon dependency if existing vpc is not provided. While the diagram illustrates a three-zone deployment, the VPC can also be provisioned in a single-zone or two-zone configuration, depending on your availability requirements.<br><br>The default configuration deploys a VPC with three zone subnets, configures the predefined ACLs, and attaches a public gateway with one of the subnets. You can also enable <b>Observability</b> for your cluster for logging and monitoring needs. <b>Secrets Manager</b> Integration can also be enabled for centrally managing Ingress subdomain certificates. Additionally, you can also create <b>Cloud Object Storage</b> instance if not providing an existing one in which object storage object gets created which acts as internal registry storage for the OpenShift cluster and bucket can be encrypted using <b>Key Protect</b> for enhanced security."
              }
            ]
